SUMMARY:Peacetown continues at HopMonk with The Flying Salvias
DESCRIPTION:They call their music “Ameri-kinda.” Thoughtful chaos is fostered\, genre boundaries are ignored\, humor is embraced\, and talent abounds\, whether performing as a duo or with their band\, The Flying Salvias Orkestra. Henry is well known for his expressive piano style and impressive chops\, and Kathleen’s voice is full of heartfelt emotional appeal whether crooning\, belting\, or just singing a story. \nAs to songwriting\, their lyrics contemplate the mystery of creation\, riff on Shakespeare\, visit a friend in jail\, compare misguided love with chameleon car paint\, or swing from depression and doubt to simple joy; all while wrapped in the rhythms of beatnik jazz\, swing\, rock\, country\, folk\, rhumba\, samba\, or whatever groove they deem appropriate at the time. This refusal to linger long in any one musical lane also holds true of the cover tune detours The Flying Salvias occasionally take. This is Ameri-kinda!
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/peacetown-continues-at-hopmonk-with-the-flying-salvias/
LOCATION:HopMonk Tavern – Sebastopol\, 230 Petaluma Ave\, Sebastopol\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
GEO:38.4012;-122.823
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=HopMonk Tavern – Sebastopol 230 Petaluma Ave Sebastopol CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=230 Petaluma Ave:geo:-122.823,38.4012
END:VEVENT
